How to host stati websites on S3 bucket 
step1: open aws account
step2: go to s3 bucket
step3:create a bucket with unique name
* Bucket name: unique
*create bucket
step4: upload files
* open the bucket 
*add files
*click on upload
step5: click on file and it shows a url  andaccess them in a global 
*Its shows error bcoz we block the public access (That's way its showing access denined)
*click on all the files which are in bucket andgo topermissions unblock the public access
*still it showing access denined bcos static website hosting is disable
step 6: Go to  bucket properties go to edit give the document name(index.html) and  enable the static website hosting
* save changes
*still shows access denined
step 7:bcoz we need to make public using ACL(Access control list)
*go to permissions scroll down until you see the object ownership
*click on edit
*enabled acl and save changes
step 8: go to bucket and tap the bucket which we create ans select all thefiles and tap on actions
* make ppublic using acl

ACCESS on the BROWSER with URL
                                                      successfully completed
           
